    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-11-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="338"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d338">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">MacVeagh</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-11-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 210.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 209, of the 22d ultimo, and
                    the Department’s No. 207, of the 6th instant, I have to acknowledge the receipt
                    of your No. 212, of the 26th ultimo, in regard to the case of Vittorio Gardella,
                    an Italian by origin, who, leaving his native land in infancy, emigrated to the
                    United States, resided here many years, became naturalized, and, returning to
                    Italy on a brief visit, leaving his family at his residence in the United
                    States, has been arrested and drafted into the Italian army.</p>
                <p>Your action in bringing the matter personally to the attention of the Italian
                    minister of foreign affairs is commended and the result awaited.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
